{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Water Quality Portal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import contextily as ctx\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "from shapely.geometry import Point\n",
    "\n",
    "from pygeohydro import WaterQuality"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "SAVE_KWDS = {\"bbox_inches\": \"tight\", \"dpi\": 300, \"facecolor\": \"w\"}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `WaterQuality` has a number of convenience methods to retrieve data from the\n",
    "web service. Since there are many parameter combinations that can be\n",
    "used to retrieve data, a general method is provided to retrieve data from\n",
    "any of the valid endpoints. You can use `get_json` to retrieve stations info\n",
    "as a `geopandas.GeoDataFrame` or `get_csv` to retrieve stations data as a\n",
    "`pandas.DataFrame`. You can construct a dictionary of the parameters and pass\n",
    "it to one of these functions. For more information on the parameters, please\n",
    "consult the [Water Quality Data documentation](https://www.waterqualitydata.us/webservices_documentation).\n",
    "For example, let's find all the stations within a bounding box that have Caffeine data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "wq = WaterQuality()\n",
    "stations = wq.station_bybbox((-92.8, 44.2, -88.9, 46.0), {\"characteristicName\": \"Caffeine\"})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Or the same criterion but within a 30 mile radius of a point:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "stations = wq.station_bydistance(-92.8, 44.2, 30, {\"characteristicName\": \"Caffeine\"})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "nbsphinx-thumbnail"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 600,
       "width": 600
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "point = gpd.GeoSeries([Point(-92.8, 44.2)], crs=\"epsg:4326\")\n",
    "point = point.to_crs(point.estimate_utm_crs())\n",
    "buff = point.buffer(30 * 1609.344)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = buff.plot(color=\"b\", edgecolor=\"black\", alpha=0.1, figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "point.plot(ax=ax, color=\"g\", marker=\"x\")\n",
    "stations.to_crs(buff.crs).plot(ax=ax, color=\"r\", marker=\"o\", facecolor=\"none\")\n",
    "ctx.add_basemap(ax, crs=buff.crs)\n",
    "ax.set_axis_off()\n",
    "ax.margins(0)\n",
    "ax.figure.set_dpi(100)\n",
    "ax.figure.savefig(\"_static/water_quality.png\", **SAVE_KWDS)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
